place.name: YARWELL
place.gazetteerText: YARWELL, a parish in Oundle district, Northampton: on the river Nen, near Wansford r. station, and 6½ miles NNE of Oundle. Post town, Wansford. Acres, with Sulehay Lodge and Locks Lodge, 1,830. Real property, £2,096. Pop., 402. Houses, 86. The manor belongs to the Earl of Westmoreland . The living is a p. curacy, annexed to Nassington. The church is ancient. There are a Methodist chapel and charities £32. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
